02:47.837 --> 02:49.167
I have some more material.

02:50.667 --> 02:52.337
It seems you will have
to identify and secure

02:52.417 --> 02:54.377
the precise location
of his death.

02:54.457 --> 02:58.127
By which I mean
the exact spot on the floor.

02:59.627 --> 03:01.297
And tell Varney 
there is definitely evidence

03:01.377 --> 03:03.797
of a transmission mirror
in the possession of the court

03:03.877 --> 03:05.377
at Targoviste.

03:05.457 --> 03:07.757
I'm working to track down
more information.

03:15.207 --> 03:17.257
From Carmilla's private stock.

03:17.337 --> 03:20.837
Now show me the 
map of hell you told me about,

03:20.917 --> 03:24.007
or I'll tell her what you've
been doing with her shoes.

03:44.337 --> 03:45.707
Morning.

03:45.797 --> 03:47.047
Evening.

03:50.507 --> 03:52.047
Fuck!

03:52.127 --> 03:54.087
You broke it.

03:54.167 --> 03:56.257
Half these billets are bad.

03:56.337 --> 03:59.877
Your vampire blacksmiths
didn't follow my specifications.

03:59.957 --> 04:04.127
A bad workman 
always blames his vampires.

04:05.587 --> 04:07.757
Don't you have 
anything better to do?

04:07.837 --> 04:09.257
Not right now.

04:09.337 --> 04:11.627
Striga and Morana
have been away for weeks,

04:11.707 --> 04:13.377
surveying the 
territories to be annexed.

04:13.457 --> 04:16.457
Carmilla is drawing maps.

04:18.877 --> 04:20.167
It seems the time
when diplomacy

04:20.257 --> 04:24.377
was required for 
anything has passed.

04:24.457 --> 04:26.667
Ah, so you're bored.

04:28.047 --> 04:30.297
No. You're worried.

04:31.417 --> 04:32.877
Shush.

04:32.957 --> 04:35.917
Lenore, are they sidelining you?

04:36.007 --> 04:37.337
They're not...

04:37.417 --> 04:39.127
It's not like that.

04:39.207 --> 04:42.007
Or, at least, they wouldn't
think of it like that.

04:42.087 --> 04:44.087
Our lives have entered
a new phase.

04:44.167 --> 04:45.507
Diplomacy, negotiations,

04:45.587 --> 04:47.877
these are things
of the past now.

04:47.957 --> 04:50.667
Hmm. Which makes you
a thing of the past,

04:50.757 --> 04:52.377
and that is bothering you.

04:53.457 --> 04:54.797
Look...

04:54.877 --> 04:58.627
Carmilla's plan
buys us security

04:58.707 --> 05:00.257
for hundreds of years.

05:02.547 --> 05:05.167
I'm a child of war, Hector.

05:06.417 --> 05:08.377
I was born
in a castle like this.

05:08.457 --> 05:10.877
My parents died
when English soldiers

05:10.957 --> 05:13.457
climbed up the toilet chutes
with knives in their teeth.

05:15.127 --> 05:17.007
I'd seen enough war
before I was five years old,

05:17.087 --> 05:20.797
and life didn't get better
after that.

05:21.917 --> 05:23.877
But I will 
never be comfortable

05:23.957 --> 05:27.377
with the idea that the 
best way to end war

05:27.457 --> 05:31.297
is to kill most of the 
people and cage the rest.

05:32.707 --> 05:34.957
Well, you are a diplomat.

05:36.297 --> 05:37.667
Well, none of this will matter

05:37.757 --> 05:39.507
if you don't make
that bloody hammer.

05:39.587 --> 05:41.337
Why can't you just wave
your fingers like a wizard

05:41.417 --> 05:43.547
to raise the dead,
or whatever?

05:43.627 --> 05:46.507
The forgemaster
works through an instrument.

05:46.587 --> 05:48.507
That may be the worst
justification

05:48.587 --> 05:51.337
for a man holding his penis
that I've ever heard.

05:51.417 --> 05:52.837
Oh, my God.

05:52.917 --> 05:54.877
And I am 200 years old.

05:54.957 --> 05:56.167
Look...

05:56.257 --> 05:57.667
I am a forgemaster.

05:57.757 --> 05:59.707
I didn't invent 
the name, all right?

05:59.797 --> 06:01.337
That's just 
what they call us.

06:01.417 --> 06:03.587
And the magic has to be 
focused through an instrument,

06:03.667 --> 06:06.257
like breath being pushed
through a flute.

06:06.337 --> 06:08.837
This isn't getting any better.

06:08.917 --> 06:11.257
I need the bloody hammer.
Is that better?

06:11.337 --> 06:12.837
So use a bloody hammer.

06:12.917 --> 06:15.417
There must be a thousand
bloody hammers around here.

06:15.507 --> 06:17.047
No, it's got to be special.

06:18.627 --> 06:20.507
Your special hammer.

06:20.587 --> 06:22.127
Would you stop?

06:22.207 --> 06:23.757
It has to be made from scratch,

06:23.837 --> 06:25.417
in a very particular way,

06:25.507 --> 06:27.297
or else it won't work.

06:27.377 --> 06:29.457
Like a flute with no holes.

06:29.547 --> 06:31.127
Right.

06:31.207 --> 06:33.207
For fingering.

06:33.297 --> 06:34.797
Would you stop?

06:34.877 --> 06:37.547
So when you blow it,
nothing comes out.

06:37.627 --> 06:38.957
Good god, woman.

06:39.047 --> 06:40.957
I'm bored, and it's fun
to horrify you.

06:41.047 --> 06:42.957
Indulge me.

06:43.047 --> 06:45.797
And think of something
to tell Carmilla.

06:45.877 --> 06:47.667
She's getting very cross.

06:47.757 --> 06:50.167
Oh, dear. How sad.

06:50.257 --> 06:52.087
Never mind.

06:52.167 --> 06:53.957
Seriously.

06:54.047 --> 06:57.917
You've supposedly been making
your magic hammer for weeks.

06:58.007 --> 07:00.377
Couldn't you make
something simpler?

07:00.457 --> 07:03.627
A stick, or a coin,
or something?

07:03.707 --> 07:05.507
We all use different things.

07:05.587 --> 07:07.837
Isaac used a knife.

07:07.917 --> 07:09.417
A hammer works better for me.

07:09.507 --> 07:13.007
Well, make it work faster.

07:13.087 --> 07:15.087
If Carmilla loses her temper,

07:15.167 --> 07:17.797
I won't be able to stand
in front of you for long.

07:17.877 --> 07:19.797
You'd stand in front of me?

07:19.877 --> 07:21.797
I've been doing it for weeks.

07:21.877 --> 07:23.917
Huh. Yes.

07:24.917 --> 07:26.257
Yes, I suppose you have.

07:26.337 --> 07:28.667
Well, thank you.

07:28.757 --> 07:30.007
I'm working on it.

07:31.297 --> 07:33.457
You know what I'm going to say.

07:33.547 --> 07:34.707
Hmm.

07:34.797 --> 07:36.297
Work faster.

07:36.377 --> 07:37.627
Yes.

07:37.707 --> 07:39.917
Yes, but it needs to be perfect,

07:40.007 --> 07:43.297
or nothing will come out
of the end.

07:43.377 --> 07:45.627
Ugh, you're disgusting.

07:57.167 --> 07:59.587
Has Hector made
his fucking hammer yet?

08:00.837 --> 08:02.377
He's still working on it.

08:02.457 --> 08:04.007
He's stalling.

08:04.087 --> 08:06.257
He's too simple for that.

08:07.917 --> 08:09.877
-No.
-No?

08:09.957 --> 08:11.707
No.

08:11.797 --> 08:14.127
There's a deviousness in him.

08:15.337 --> 08:16.917
Would you suspect a rag doll

08:17.007 --> 08:19.547
of planning to steal
your coin purse?

08:19.627 --> 08:24.377
You mistake that puppy thing
for being placid and stupid.

08:25.457 --> 08:26.957
He can kill.

08:27.047 --> 08:29.257
He tried, once.

08:29.337 --> 08:31.457
It was half-hearted at best.

08:32.667 --> 08:34.167
Mm. See?

08:34.257 --> 08:36.417
See what? You weren't there.

08:36.507 --> 08:38.507
He was confused and frightened,

08:38.587 --> 08:40.667
and barely even knew
what he was doing.

08:41.507 --> 08:43.007
I'm warning you.

08:43.087 --> 08:44.587
All right?

08:44.667 --> 08:46.667
I'm just warning you.

08:46.757 --> 08:50.257
Please, would Dracula have kept
him around in his own castle

08:50.337 --> 08:52.207
if he were that dangerous?

08:54.707 --> 08:57.087
I would 
have liked that castle.

08:57.167 --> 08:58.357
Dracula's castle?

08:59.377 --> 09:00.757
Yes.

09:00.837 --> 09:03.837
I didn't see 
alot of it, in the end.

09:03.917 --> 09:05.127
But I'm sure it was full

09:05.207 --> 09:08.507
of interesting
and wonderful things.

09:08.587 --> 09:12.587
I am compelled to point out that
you already have a nice castle.

09:12.667 --> 09:14.757
Why would you want his?

09:14.837 --> 09:18.837
Because I take things away
from stupid, evil old men.

09:18.917 --> 09:20.207
It's what I do.

09:20.297 --> 09:22.047
I've always done it.

09:22.127 --> 09:24.627
They deserve to lose everything.

09:24.707 --> 09:27.797
And I deserve to have
all their stuff.

09:27.877 --> 09:30.417
You could just 
make new things.

09:30.507 --> 09:33.167
Why would I waste my time,

09:33.257 --> 09:36.007
when I can just take
whatever I want

09:36.087 --> 09:38.457
and then kill whoever had them?

09:41.007 --> 09:42.547
Look at my map.

09:42.627 --> 09:44.297
From here to Braila.

09:44.377 --> 09:48.957
That land and those villages
and towns belong to old men.

09:49.047 --> 09:50.207
All of them.

09:50.297 --> 09:52.377
And I'm going to take them.

09:52.457 --> 09:57.667
This castle belonged
to a stupid, evil old man.

09:58.667 --> 09:59.877
I took it.

09:59.957 --> 10:02.377
The land from here to Braila,

10:02.457 --> 10:05.127
ruled by stupid old men.

10:05.207 --> 10:10.047
Devastated by one single
stupid old man.

10:11.417 --> 10:12.917
There for the taking.

10:13.007 --> 10:16.797
And will you be happy
when you have all that?

10:18.377 --> 10:20.837
Just look at this.

10:22.127 --> 10:23.877
Look.

10:23.957 --> 10:28.087
Do you know how many regional
vampire rulers died at Braila?

10:28.167 --> 10:30.707
I didn't know
I had to count them.

10:30.797 --> 10:32.797
Well, you should.

10:32.877 --> 10:34.507
It was a lot.

10:34.587 --> 10:36.417
These are just the ones
I'm certain of.

10:37.757 --> 10:39.167
These little flags?

10:39.257 --> 10:40.707
That's right.

10:40.797 --> 10:43.707
All these regions
without direct vampire rule.

10:43.797 --> 10:47.457
Just waiting for 
someone to take control.

10:47.547 --> 10:51.207
Surely their underlings will
raise someone up into command.

10:51.297 --> 10:54.417
Unless we were there first.

10:54.507 --> 10:56.507
Why would we do that?

10:56.587 --> 10:58.667
This is the world, Lenore.

11:00.127 --> 11:03.377
We could take the 
entire world for our own.

11:04.587 --> 11:06.377
Wouldn't you want that?

11:09.547 --> 11:11.337
I don't know.

11:11.417 --> 11:14.957
The "sweet little girl" act
doesn't work on me, Lenore.

11:15.047 --> 11:16.877
Try again.

11:16.957 --> 11:18.127
I really don't know.

11:18.207 --> 11:21.957
I...I never thought
about anything that big before.

11:22.047 --> 11:23.587
Start.

11:23.667 --> 11:25.507
Answer my question first.

11:26.507 --> 11:28.257
Will you be happy

11:28.337 --> 11:30.667
when you have all this?

11:36.457 --> 11:40.047
The first part of my life
was men taking things from me.

11:41.837 --> 11:44.167
And then I took their lives.

11:44.257 --> 11:45.917
And their things.

11:46.007 --> 11:48.377
And their homes.

11:48.457 --> 11:50.167
And then we took Styria.

11:50.257 --> 11:52.877
After which
we formed our little enclave.

11:52.957 --> 11:55.007
We tried not to do more harm.

11:55.087 --> 11:56.917
We tried to make a home.

11:57.007 --> 11:58.877
And when the wolf people
came from the north,

11:58.957 --> 12:00.417
and the armies
from the west,

12:00.507 --> 12:02.457
and every other 
bastard came for us.

12:03.707 --> 12:05.047
And we asked for help.

12:06.547 --> 12:08.957
What did the rest
of the vampire world say?

12:09.047 --> 12:11.917
"Bloody women," they said.

12:12.007 --> 12:15.337
"Let them die," they said.

12:15.417 --> 12:18.627
So I'm going to take 
everything from everybody.

12:19.707 --> 12:21.457
I was in Dracula's castle.

12:21.547 --> 12:23.957
I went there to see
what I could get out of it.

12:24.047 --> 12:25.507
Get some more power
for myself.

12:25.587 --> 12:27.957
Some more security for us.

12:28.047 --> 12:31.377
What I found was him
and his people just fucking it up.

12:31.457 --> 12:32.917
And I saw, right there,

12:33.007 --> 12:34.547
that I could take 
the world away from him

12:34.627 --> 12:36.337
and have it for myself!

12:38.417 --> 12:39.837
The world, Lenore!

12:44.047 --> 12:46.297
Will I be happy
when I've done that?

12:47.297 --> 12:48.627
I don't know.

12:49.707 --> 12:52.087
I don't know if I even care.

12:53.877 --> 12:56.127
But I will have everything
that they had.

12:56.207 --> 12:59.087
And they will all be dead.

13:00.417 --> 13:03.337
I will have the world I want, Lenore,

13:03.417 --> 13:04.667
and that...

13:06.007 --> 13:07.587
that will be enough.

13:07.667 --> 13:10.507
Having everything
will be enough.

13:10.587 --> 13:12.207
Having the world.

13:13.507 --> 13:15.417
And all of them being dead.

13:16.707 --> 13:19.707
Is this what it was all for?

13:21.297 --> 13:23.797
What on earth did you think
this was all about?

13:38.707 --> 13:40.297
I think he finished his hammer.

13:51.417 --> 13:53.047
Well, this won't be terrible,

13:53.127 --> 13:54.757
for one night.

13:54.837 --> 13:57.417
Look, it's even got
an attractive window.

13:57.507 --> 13:59.167
In the roof.

13:59.257 --> 14:01.167
Perfect. Sleeping under starlight.

14:03.127 --> 14:05.457
And targeted by bird shit.

14:05.547 --> 14:07.957
I haven't seen
a single bird since we got here.

14:08.047 --> 14:09.507
Really?

14:09.587 --> 14:11.667
I can hear something
up in the rafters.

14:21.837 --> 14:23.297
Oh, shit.

14:29.087 --> 14:30.377
Here we go again.

14:30.457 --> 14:31.917
Try not to burn the barn down

14:32.007 --> 14:33.257
while we're in it.

14:34.337 --> 14:35.707
I did that one time.

14:38.007 --> 14:39.707
One time was enough.

14:40.497 --> 14:42.257
It had a giant spider in it.

14:44.667 --> 14:45.917
It wasn't giant.

14:48.937 --> 14:49.957
It was ten feet tall.

14:53.417 --> 14:55.547
Maybe eight.

14:55.627 --> 14:58.127
So, what, eight feet tall
isn't giant?

15:01.047 --> 15:02.337
Fuck me.

15:02.417 --> 15:03.917
These bastards again.

15:04.007 --> 15:06.297
They're very good,
aren't they?

15:07.297 --> 15:08.237
They're annoying.

15:08.917 --> 15:11.007
And young.

15:11.087 --> 15:12.457
I suppose.

15:13.627 --> 15:15.507
Pretty.

15:15.587 --> 15:17.757
Smooth skin.

15:17.837 --> 15:19.667
What, did you want to nip down
there and marry them?

15:21.087 --> 15:23.547
I want to wear their skin.

15:35.667 --> 15:37.877
Are you sure you don't want me
to set fire to things?

15:39.377 --> 15:41.417
I'm thinking it might
be an option now.

16:24.757 --> 16:25.757
Whoa!

18:20.087 --> 18:21.547
Thanks.

18:21.627 --> 18:25.257
We somehow managed
to walk right into that one.

18:25.337 --> 18:29.007
It wasn't for you.
The trap was for us.

18:29.087 --> 18:30.917
I'm Trevor Belmont.

18:31.007 --> 18:33.587
This is Sypha Belnades.

18:33.667 --> 18:37.587
Zamfir. Head guard to the
Underground Court of Targoviste.

18:37.667 --> 18:39.007
The what?

18:39.087 --> 18:40.707
The ruling family
of Targoviste

18:40.797 --> 18:43.207
survived Dracula's
first assault.

18:43.297 --> 18:45.377
But, later, the vampires
and night creatures came,

18:45.457 --> 18:46.757
and it was safer to move them

18:46.837 --> 18:48.797
into the catacombs
under the city.

18:48.877 --> 18:50.627
I'm amazed anyone's still alive,

18:50.707 --> 18:52.507
let alone the royal family.

18:52.587 --> 18:55.417
I run the resistance
against the devils.

18:55.507 --> 18:59.337
Hell itself has attempted
to curse our golden city,

18:59.417 --> 19:02.087
but we will not allow it.

19:02.167 --> 19:04.587
I'm sorry 
about your people.

19:04.667 --> 19:06.207
We are 
grateful for your aid.

19:06.297 --> 19:07.917
They died for the Court.

19:09.417 --> 19:11.547
Well, they did die.

19:11.627 --> 19:14.047
They were your 
friends, were they not?

19:15.877 --> 19:17.707
We have been
following signs of some plot

19:17.797 --> 19:19.337
to return Dracula to Earth.

19:19.417 --> 19:21.667
Does this mean
anything to you?

19:21.757 --> 19:24.797
There's a nest of vampires
in the city who wish it.

19:24.877 --> 19:27.007
They are trying to find
the Underground Court,

19:27.087 --> 19:30.587
to ransack its many magical
treasures for their cause.

19:30.667 --> 19:33.417
We would be interested
in seeing this court.

19:33.507 --> 19:35.377
To evaluate 
the threat.

19:36.547 --> 19:37.917
We would be delighted

19:38.007 --> 19:40.087
to have you join
the royal struggle.

19:40.167 --> 19:41.757
Well, good.

19:41.837 --> 19:44.257
Help us save Targoviste.

19:44.337 --> 19:45.707
Gladly.

19:45.797 --> 19:47.047
But not yet.

19:47.127 --> 19:48.837
I cannot take you to the court

19:48.917 --> 19:51.127
until I am certain
I can trust you.

19:58.257 --> 19:59.627
Oh, shit.

20:05.547 --> 20:09.087
Well, she was...interesting.

20:09.167 --> 20:11.757
You mean a little crazy.

20:12.417 --> 20:14.007
Oh, yes.

20:14.087 --> 20:15.877
You poor bastards.

20:16.877 --> 20:19.627
-What are you doing?
-Nothing.

20:19.707 --> 20:22.547
Oh, I know you're not
robbing the dead.

20:22.627 --> 20:24.547
Absolutely not.

20:36.337 --> 20:38.377
And I've seen enough
glowing rocks for a while.

20:38.457 --> 20:40.167
They lead to trouble.

20:40.257 --> 20:41.587
Quite right too.

20:41.667 --> 20:42.667
Why invite trouble?

20:43.547 --> 20:45.257
We never do that.
